From 5a6c3a8cd7243661f1c816cf9e8c9f4db8d18c7d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sen Wang <sen@ti.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 16:33:16 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] drm/bridge: sii902x: Convert to DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI
 framework

Convert the SiI9022 HDMI bridge driver from the legacy hdmi-codec
platform device and manual AVI infoframe packing to the modern
DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI and DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI_AUDIO framework.

The DRM bridge connector framework now manages infoframe lifecycle
and creates the HDMI audio codec device. A legacy hdmi-codec platform
device is still registered at probe for backwards compatibility with
existing DTS bindings that use sound-dai = <&sii9022> in
simple-audio-card or audio-graph-card nodes. When the display
controller uses DRM_BRIDGE_ATTACH_NO_CONNECTOR (the modern path),
the legacy device is unregistered in attach to avoid duplicates.

The atomic_enable function is restructured to use two mutex sections
instead of three: one for video timing and D0 power-up, and one that
combines the AVI infoframe write and TMDS enable for the legacy
connector path.

Signed-off-by: Sen Wang <s-wang12@ti.com>
